# shadcn-vue Component Guidelines

## Component Preference Rules
- **Always prefer shadcn-vue components** over custom implementations or other UI libraries.
- **Check existing shadcn-vue components first** before creating new UI elements.
- **Use the shadcn-vue CLI** to add new components when needed: `npx shadcn-vue@latest add <component-name>`.

## Available Components
The project has the following shadcn-vue components available in `@/components/ui/`:
- Avatar, Badge, Breadcrumb, Button, Card, Checkbox, Collapsible
- Dialog, Dropdown Menu, Input, Label, Navigation Menu, Pin Input
- Select, Separator, Sheet, Sidebar, Skeleton, Switch, Tooltip

## Component Usage Guidelines
- **Import from `@/components/ui`** - Use the established import pattern.
- **Follow shadcn-vue patterns** - Use the component composition patterns as designed.
- **Extend with variants** - Use `class-variance-authority` for component variants when needed.
- **Maintain consistency** - All UI components should follow the same design system.

## When to Add New Components
- **Before creating custom UI** - Always check if a shadcn-vue component exists.
- **Use shadcn-vue CLI** - Add new components using the official CLI tool.
- **Follow naming conventions** - Use the established component naming patterns.

## Component Customization
- **Use CSS variables** - Leverage the CSS variable system for theming.
- **Extend with Tailwind** - Use Tailwind classes for additional styling.
- **Maintain accessibility** - shadcn-vue components include accessibility features by default.

